The Federal Mortgage Bank of Nigeria (FMBN) said it has refunded over N9 billion National Housing Fund (NHF) to over 200,000 retirees across the country. The Managing Director of the bank, Architect Ahmed Dangiwa said this yesterday in Abuja at the Affordable Housing Summit, organised by Zvecan Homes and Estate yesterday in Abuja. The summit witnessed the unveiling of a 3000 housing units in four locations in the FCT. Dangiwa represented by Mr Oladapo Fakeye said every NHF contributed by civil servants was refundable with interest once they attain 60 years. He said the summit was critical to briefing housing deficit in Nigeria as it would generate solutions for the development of the housing sector.